  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 26 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 9 critical, 10 high, 9 medium, 11 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR); plus 16 other bases. 9 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and cold‑temperature performance penalties  — most notably around Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR). Network hotspots: Trondheim Airport, Værnes (TRD/ENVA), Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Nuremberg (NUE/EDDN), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH) and 21 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Trondheim Airport, Værnes (TRD/ENVA), Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO) and 9 others.",
